  • Field Details

    • MSG_REGISTER_CLIENT

      public static final int MSG_REGISTER_CLIENT
      Command to the service to register a client, to start receiving messages from the service.

      The client sends its own Messenger instance. It will be used to deliver app-generated events like freeze status or new images.

      Note: The given Messenger will be used to deliver the reply for this command but will not be used to deliver replies to subsequent commands. Use the individual command's replyTo field for that purpose.

      Message parameter(s)
      ParameterTypeDescriptionNotes
      Message.replyToMessenger Client's Messenger where the service will send app-generated events. Mandatory, registration will fail if missing.
      Message.arg1intCallback parameter included in the reply message.Optional

      Return: 0 = success, -1 = failure.

      See Also:
      • Constant Field Values

    • MSG_UNREGISTER_CLIENT

      public static final int MSG_UNREGISTER_CLIENT
      Command to the service to unregister a client, to stop receiving messages from the service.
      Message parameter(s)
      ParameterTypeDescriptionNotes
      Message.replyTo Messenger Client's Messenger previously registered with MSG_REGISTER_CLIENT. This messenger will be used one last time to deliver the reply for this command. Mandatory
      Message.arg1intCallback parameter included in the reply message.Optional

      Return: 0 = success, -1 = failure.

    • MSG_CONFIGURE_IMAGE

      public static final int MSG_CONFIGURE_IMAGE
      Command to the service to set the image rendering configuration.

      This will cause the service to start imaging.

      Message parameter(s)
      ParameterTypeDescriptionNotes
      Bundle[KEY_IMAGE_SIZE] android.util.Size The requested rendering size. Mandatory
      Bundle[KEY_COMPRESSION_TYPE] java.lang.String One of the predefined COMPRESSION_TYPE_* constants. Optional, default: DEFAULT_COMPRESSION_TYPE.
      Bundle[KEY_COMPRESSION_QUALITY] int The compression quality between 0 (worst quality) and 100 (best quality). Optional, default: DEFAULT_COMPRESSION_QUALITY.
      Message.replyToMessengerIf set, MSG_RETURN_STATUS will be sent to this messenger.Optional
      Message.arg1intCallback parameter included in the reply message.Optional
      Added in Clarius App 8.0.1
      Bundle[KEY_SEPARATE_OVERLAYS] boolean Flag for separating overlays. If set, two images are sent: one with overlays and one without. Optional, default: DEFAULT_SEPARATE_OVERLAYS.

      Return: 0 = success, -1 = failure.

      See Also:

    • MSG_COPY_RAW_DATA

      public static final int MSG_COPY_RAW_DATA
      Get a copy of a raw data archive.

      This message is used to obtain a copy of a raw data archive received with message MSG_RAW_DATA_AVAILABLE. The reply will be delivered with message MSG_RAW_DATA_COPIED.

      Message parameter(s)
      ParameterTypeDescriptionNotes
      Bundle[KEY_CAPTURE_ID] java.lang.String The capture identifier in UUID format obtained from MSG_RAW_DATA_AVAILABLE. Mandatory
      Bundle[KEY_WRITABLE_URI] android.net.Uri A file URI where the service will write the raw data archive. It must have write permissions for the Clarius App. Mandatory
      Message.replyToMessengerClient's Messenger where the reply will be sent.Mandatory
      Message.arg1intCallback parameter included in the reply message.Optional

      Refer to https://developer.android.com/training/secure-file-sharing to create a writable URI.

      Since:
      Clarius App 9.2.0
      See Also:

      public static final int MSG_SCAN_AREA_CHANGED
      Message to the client when the scan area changes.

      The scan area allows 3rd party apps to know where the B-image is displayed, this can be used to display a custom overlay.

    • MSG_RAW_DATA_AVAILABLE

      public static final int MSG_RAW_DATA_AVAILABLE
      New raw data data available to download.

      Raw data workflow:

      1. When new raw data is available, the service will send MSG_RAW_DATA_AVAILABLE with a capture ID.
      2. To get a copy of the raw data, send MSG_COPY_RAW_DATA to the service with the capture ID in parameter and a writable URI.
      3. The service will write the corresponding raw data in the given writable URI and send MSG_RAW_DATA_COPIED on completion.
      Message parameter(s)
      ParameterTypeDescription
      Bundle[KEY_CAPTURE_ID] java.lang.String The capture identifier in UUID format (without braces).
      Bundle[KEY_FILE_NAME] java.lang.String The archive file name.
      Bundle[KEY_SIZE_BYTES] long.lang.String The archive size, in bytes.

      To download the archive, send MSG_COPY_RAW_DATA with the capture ID as parameter.

      Since:
      Clarius App 9.2.0
      See Also:
      • Constant Field Values

    • MSG_RAW_DATA_COPIED

      public static final int MSG_RAW_DATA_COPIED
      Reply to queries MSG_COPY_RAW_DATA.
      Message parameter(s)
      ParameterTypeDescription

      Optional parameter(s) in case of an error
      ParameterTypeDescription
      Bundle[KEY_ERROR_MESSAGE] java.lang.String The error description in English.

    • USER_FN_SET_DEPTH

      public static final String USER_FN_SET_DEPTH
      User function to set the depth, to be used with messages MSG_USER_FN.
      MSG_USER_FN parameter
      ParameterTypeDescription
      Bundle[KEY_USER_PARAM] double The target depth in centimeters.

      Note: The value will be clipped if it is out of range.

      See Also:
      • Constant Field Values

    • USER_FN_SET_GAIN

      public static final String USER_FN_SET_GAIN
      User function to set the gain, to be used with messages MSG_USER_FN.
      MSG_USER_FN parameter
      ParameterTypeDescription
      Bundle[KEY_USER_PARAM] double The target gain as documented below.

      The gain range depends if auto-gain is on or off:

      • auto gain off: the gain is the central TGC value in the range [-20 20]
      • auto gain on: the gain is the gamma value in the range [-0.5 0.5]
      See Also:
      • Constant Field Values
